main event: A witness observed a large unidentified object in the sky near Waco, Texas on May 9, 1960.
interesting points: The object was described as having no wings or tail and was approximately 20 times the size of a B-57 aircraft., The sighting lasted only 1-2 seconds at dusk., The object changed course from east to north without apparent change in direction., The witness heard the sound of a jet aircraft before looking up to see the object., The report was classified as insufficient data for a conclusive evaluation.
sighted object: one unidentified object in the sky
witness description: The witness was knowledgeable about aircraft and works in automatic farm equipment sales and installation.
